    <section id="governance">
      <h2>Wu Xing in Governance and History</h2>
      <div class="quote-card">
        <p>Each dynasty was associated with an element, and its successor represented the conquering element &mdash; Qin claimed Water over Zhou's Fire, Han claimed Earth over Qin's Water.</p>
        <cite>Zou Yan's theory of dynastic succession through the overcoming cycle, intertwined with the Mandate of Heaven (<span class="chinese-char">天命</span>)</cite>
